cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SI 

This paper deals with privacy and security concerns related to web search, specifically the ability of users to maintain plausible deniability of their interests. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) since it involves the use of search engine algorithms to learn about user interests. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on user behavior and mental health, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and the use of proxy topics as a defense technique, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
